# Backend and Database Completion

We have successfully integrated the application with the database by converting the mock data into a live system powered by Supabase.

## Changes Made

- **Database Migrations:**
  - Created `auctions` table to store item listings, prices, categories, and sellers.
  - Created `bids` table to link specific bids to the auction and the user who placed them.
  - Set up Row Level Security (RLS) on both tables to ensure data integrity and security.
  - Created a robust `place_bid` stored procedure to securely update both the `bids` table and the `auctions` current price and bid count transactionally.

- **Type Safety & Frontend Preparation:**
  - Added definitions for `auctions` and `bids` to the TypeScript database schema [types.ts](file:///d:/Web%20Dev/auctify-bid-space-main/src/integrations/supabase/types.ts).

- **React Application Integration:**
  - **[Auction.tsx](file:///d:/Web%20Dev/auctify-bid-space-main/src/pages/Auction.tsx):** Hooked up fetching using `@tanstack/react-query` to pull live active listings from the `auctions` table instead of using localized dummy data. Ensured new listings are properly inserted into the `auctions` table.
  - **[AuctionProduct.tsx](file:///d:/Web%20Dev/auctify-bid-space-main/src/pages/AuctionProduct.tsx):** Integrated live fetching for detailed views. Implemented calling the `place_bid` remote procedure to correctly add bids. Also added Supabase **Realtime Subscriptions** on the auction explicitly so that the UI can update live when other users place a bid (`current_price` and `bid_count` instantly syncing without refreshing).

## What Was Tested

- ✅ TypeScript linting (`npm run lint`) to ensure codebase correctness. Fixed multiple type mismatches and legacy errors across files.
- ✅ Application build phase (`npm run build`) to ensure there are no bundling or production errors.

## Next Steps

If you would like, you can now push your new migration to your Supabase project (if running a local or linked project) using `supabase db push`.

The backend integration is ready to go! Ensure your environment [.env](file:///d:/Web%20Dev/auctify-bid-space-main/.env) variables contain the correct production Supabase URL to see real data.
